# Angular 20+ — mandatory standards

Official reference: [next.angular.dev](https://next.angular.dev).

## Syntax and components

- Modern control flow in templates: `@if`, `@for`, `@switch` / `@case`. **Do not** use legacy structural directives (`*ngIf`, `*ngFor`, `*ngSwitch`, etc.).
- Dependency injection: **only** `inject()` from functions or class fields. **Do not** inject via the constructor.
- Components: `@Component({ standalone: true, ... })` (plus any other metadata the project uses).
- Reactive state: use `signal`, `computed`, and `effect` when they improve clarity or performance; do not force signals where an Observable-based flow is a better fit.

## Zoneless

- The app runs **without Zone.js**: do not assume automatic change detection from zone patching. Prefer `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`, signals, the `async` pipe, or other explicit triggers consistent with the project.

## Asynchrony

- **Always Observables (RxJS)** in services and components: do not use Promises as the public contract or `async`/`await` to orchestrate business flows. If an external API only returns a Promise, adapt it at the boundary with RxJS operators (e.g. `from`, `defer`) and expose an Observable to the rest of the app.

## Forms

- `ngModel` / template-driven forms: only for **small or quick** forms.
- **Large or complex** forms: **Reactive Forms** (`FormControl`, `FormGroup`, `FormArray`, validators, etc.).

## Quick examples

```typescript
// ❌ Avoid
constructor(private svc: MyService) {}

// ✅ Prefer
private readonly svc = inject(MyService);
```

```html
<!-- ❌ Avoid -->
<div *ngIf="visible()">...</div>

<!-- ✅ Prefer -->
@if (visible()) {
  <div>...</div>
}
```
